WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.540
Welcome back. In this lesson, we will install OpenClaw in Windows 11 Virtual Machine, which is running in Oracle VirtualBox.

00:00:08.860 --> 00:00:12.180
It is recommended to use virtual machines for several reasons.

00:00:12.460 --> 00:00:20.260
First, you can create snapshots and then revert back to these snapshots after completing your reverse engineering or malware analysis projects.

00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:29.160
Secondly, if OpenClaw accidentally damages your system or makes unwanted changes, you can also easily revert back to earlier snapshots.

00:00:29.160 --> 00:00:32.000
This is my Windows 11 virtual machine.

00:00:32.280 --> 00:00:34.440
The first thing I did was to take a snapshot.

00:00:36.610 --> 00:00:38.870
This is the official website for OpenClaw.

00:00:39.490 --> 00:00:42.730
And this is the official documentation for OpenClaw.

00:00:43.050 --> 00:00:46.330
If you need help, you can refer to this documentation.

00:00:52.790 --> 00:00:56.710
OpenClaw recommends Node version 24 at time of this recording.

00:00:57.330 --> 00:01:01.950
My virtual machine has no Node installed, but you do not need to manually install it.

00:01:02.390 --> 00:01:08.840
Instead, use the one-liner installation command here.

00:01:08.920 --> 00:01:17.850
It will automatically install Node.js.

00:01:17.850 --> 00:01:23.510
Next we will open a PowerShell command line as administrator, search for PowerShell, then

00:01:23.510 --> 00:01:35.060
right click and run as administrator, copy the one-liner installation command and paste

00:01:35.060 --> 00:01:40.020
it into PowerShell and hit enter, and then just wait for it to install.

00:01:40.020 --> 00:01:41.860
It will take about 5 minutes.

00:01:41.860 --> 00:01:47.500
Take note that, for Windows installation, the OpenClaw documentation requires administrator

00:01:47.500 --> 00:02:07.900
PowerShell. Installing it without administrator PowerShell might produce error. It has now finished

00:02:07.900 --> 00:02:13.820
installing and now doing the setup phase. Use your arrow key to select yes and hit enter.

00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:28.720
Select quick start and hit enter. Next, select your model provider. There are two ways to set up the

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:35.420
AI provider. OpenAI allows you to use your ChatGPT subscription to link to OpenClaw. All the other

00:02:35.420 --> 00:02:40.740
companies require you to use API key. For this course, I will use the ChatGPT OAuth

00:02:40.740 --> 00:02:45.100
but for those of you who prefer to use API keys, I will now show you where to

00:02:45.100 --> 00:02:51.140
get those API keys. For Claude API key, go to this page after logging in and click

00:02:51.140 --> 00:02:57.500
on the button get API key. Then just top up some money and get your API key. API

00:02:57.500 --> 00:03:02.660
keys are pay as you go. So each time you call the API, it will use your credit and

00:03:02.660 --> 00:03:05.020
and when credit is low, you need to top up.

00:03:05.680 --> 00:03:07.840
Another option is to use Open Router.

00:03:08.320 --> 00:03:11.180
With Open Router, you just need to get one API key,

00:03:11.480 --> 00:03:14.260
and you will then have access to more than 300 models.

00:03:28.260 --> 00:03:33.280
Now coming back to the setup, I will use my ChatGPT subscription via OAuth.

00:03:33.840 --> 00:03:37.280
So I scroll down and select OpenAI Codex and hit enter.

00:03:42.960 --> 00:03:45.920
It will open a browser to ask you to log in to authenticate.

00:03:46.420 --> 00:03:50.140
Then you need to click continue to sign in to Codex with ChatGPT.

00:03:53.400 --> 00:03:59.260
Then, head back to the setup screen and under Default Model, select Keep Current which is

00:03:59.260 --> 00:04:02.460
OpenAI Codex GPT 5.4.

00:04:02.460 --> 00:04:03.720
Hit enter.

00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:08.940
If you had chose Other Providers, it would have asked you to paste in your API key.

00:04:08.940 --> 00:04:11.840
Now it will ask you to select Channel.

00:04:11.840 --> 00:04:16.800
This will link your OpenClaw to social media for example Telegram, WhatsApp or Discord.

00:04:16.800 --> 00:04:21.980
You can skip for now and set it up later if you want, but I will select Telegram.

00:04:21.980 --> 00:04:37.680
follow the instructions. Open telegram and search for botfather. Enter the command newbot.

00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:52.800
Enter a name for your bot. Then enter a username for your bot. Click on the bot token to copy

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:59.960
it to clipboard. Then go back to the setup screen. Select enter telegram bot token. Then

00:04:59.960 --> 00:05:15.740
paste the bot token here. Next, for search provider, just scroll down and select Tavily

00:05:15.740 --> 00:05:30.480
search and hit enter. Go to the Tavily website and sign up for free to get an API key. Copy your API

00:05:30.480 --> 00:05:44.560
key and paste it into the setup screen. For the configure skills, use arrow key to select no and

00:05:44.560 --> 00:05:53.540
hit enter. We can configure this later. For hooks, use spacebar one by one to select all and then hit

00:05:53.540 --> 00:06:19.200
enter. It will install the gateway service and start it and finally onboarding is complete

00:06:21.960 --> 00:06:36.400
close the terminal and open a cmd line terminal. Open the web ui by typing open claw dashboard

00:06:41.360 --> 00:07:16.080
and you can chat with open claw here. accessnswer the questions tell it its name and also your name

00:07:23.460 --> 00:07:37.400
tell it what you want it to be. Ask it to choose an emoji for itself

00:07:50.610 --> 00:07:53.170
Tell it what type of personality you'd like it to have.

00:08:08.040 --> 00:08:13.080
Now, let's test Telegram. You can either use your mobile phone or the desktop.

00:08:15.990 --> 00:08:19.990
Click on the Telegram bot link that Botfather created for you.

00:08:21.430 --> 00:08:33.160
Then click start. It will ask you to pair. Just copy the pairing command and paste it into a

00:08:33.160 --> 00:08:50.680
CMD terminal and it will pair the Telegram account. If you have any errors like what

00:08:50.680 --> 00:08:57.400
you are seeing here for me regarding PowerShell, just ask OpenClaw how to fix. I ran the PowerShell

00:08:57.400 --> 00:09:02.680
command that it recommended and it fixed the permission issue. After making any changes,

00:09:02.680 --> 00:09:08.520
be sure to restart the OpenClaw Gateway for it to take effect. Use the command OpenClaw Gateway

00:09:08.520 --> 00:09:15.560
restart. When you reboot your PC, OpenClaw Gateway service should auto restart. If it does not auto

00:09:15.560 --> 00:09:23.160
restart do the command: open claw gateway status then open claw gateway start. Remember, if you need

00:09:23.160 --> 00:09:27.880
to do anything or need any help with the configuration just ask open claw. It has

00:09:27.880 --> 00:09:34.120
access to your machine and can directly fix it. That's all for this lesson thank you for watching.

